11/04/2003
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- NATO Secretary General George Robertson says Republika Srpska's (RS) President Dragan Cavic told him that an arrest warrant has been filed against former Bosnian Serb leader Radovan Karadzic. Robertson and the ambassadors of the North Atlantic Council paid a brief visit to BiH on Thursday (10 April). Following talks with Cavic in Sarajevo, Robertson said that Cavic "considered himself personally responsible" for Karadzic's arrest.
In other news, NATO-led peacekeepers in BiH arrested a Bosnian Muslim wanted for war crimes and flew him to The Hague, NATO and UN officials said Friday. Naser Oric, 35, was the wartime army commander in Srebrenica, where the worst massacre of Muslim civilians during the 1992-1995 war occurred. Oric led the defence of the Muslim enclave of Srebrenica against Bosnian Serb forces and is accused of committing war crimes against Serbs. (AP, AFP, OHR Sources - 11/04/03; PBS BiH, RTRS, AFP - 10/04/03)
